						               													<description>Crazy Eights with a pirate twist!&amp;#10;Deal the cards and match numbers and suits. The first player to get rid of all his cards first, wins! It&amp;rsquo;s simple, but it&amp;rsquo;s not easy! Lay down a Crazy Nate 8 and you can turn the game to your advantage. &amp;#10;Each player plays a card of the same number or suit as the top card in the discard pile. For example, if the top card is a 4 of Scurvy Sam, the player may discard any 4 or any Scurvy Sam. If the player does not have a 4 or a Scurvy Sam, he must pick one card from the draw pile, unless he has a Crazy Nate 8. A player may discard a Crazy Nate 8 and change the suit to any suit of his choosing. The first player to get rid of all of his cards and shout &amp;quot;Shiver me timbers&amp;quot; wins!&amp;#10;For a more challenging game you can add variations - for instance, when a 2 is played the next player must play 2 cards and if he can&amp;rsquo;t, he must draw 2 cards. Variations are listed in the instructions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Components:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     48 cards&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
